The defendant Warren J Schaller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Cash bail applied to costs, paid in full. Balance to be refunded to poster.

Submit to an AODA assessment, follow through with any treatment, counseling.  No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia. Comply with random urine screens.  Maintain absolute sobriety.

Early Termination of Probation is Not allowed. Cases 15CM1890 and 16CM673 were dismissed and read in. Comply with any mental health/psychological evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate. Maintain employment and/or school combination. 
No Violent or abusive contact with any family member. Follow through with any treatment or counseling recommended by agent. 
  If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.

Defendant Warren J Schaller in court with attorney Mark Emil Kershek.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a no contest plea to count # 1. Court performs plea colloquy and finds defendant guilty of count #1. Cases 16CM673, 15CM1890 are dismissed and read in. State gives sentencing recommendations. Atty Kershek makes statements regarding sentencing. Defendant's son makes statements. Defendant makes Statements. The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT#1:

WITHHELD SENTENCE:   

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
____Early termination will not be allowed. 
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No violent or abusive contact with any family member
____Mental Heath / Psychological Evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate

CONDITION TIME: 30 days-Non-working hours with standard release conditions, STAYED for use of agent with court permission. .
